{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:31:12.203869+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a walkthrough of the three migrations in this repository, in the order they'd be applied:\n\n---\n\n### Migration 001 — `001_create_users.sql`\n\nCreates the **`users`** table, which is the foundational table for the application:\n\n| Column | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | Auto-incrementing primary key |\n| `email` | `TEXT` | Must be unique and not null |\n| `display_name` | `TEXT` | Optional (nullable) |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | Defaults to the current time (`now()`) |\n\nThis is the base entity — every other table depends on it.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 002 — `002_create_sessions.sql`\n\nCreates the **`sessions`** table, which tracks user login sessions:\n\n| Column | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | `UUID` | Primary key (random UUID, not sequential) |\n| `user_id` | `BIGINT` | Foreign key → `users(id)` with `ON DELETE CASCADE` |\n| `issued_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | Defaults to `now()` |\n| `expires_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | Must be set explicitly (no default) |\n\nThe `ON DELETE CASCADE` means if a user is deleted, all their sessions are automatically cleaned up. The schema implies the application likely checks `expires_at` to invalidate stale sessions.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 003 — `003_add_session_index.sql`\n\nAdds an **index** on the `sessions.user_id` column:\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\nThis speeds up queries that look up sessions by user (e.g., \"find all active sessions for this user\" or \"invalidate all sessions for user X\"). Without this index, every such query would require a full table scan on `sessions`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of the evolution\n\nThe three migrations tell a clear story of incremental development:\n\n1. **001** — Stand up the core `users` table.\n2. **002** — Add session management (login/auth support), with a FK relationship back to users.\n3. **003** — Performance tuning: index the foreign key column so session-by-user lookups are fast.\n\nIt's a clean, well-structured set — nothing fancy, just good foundational schema design.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 540, "prompt_tokens": 5990, "total_tokens": 6530, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 15, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5632, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006458052, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001760052, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0004698}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864261-w5xuODfvdp8DH2c4E8hX", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c8-1aa1-7cf2-b12b-5880aa49d1d3-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5990, "output_tokens": 540, "total_tokens": 6530, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5632}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 15}}}}]}}}
